In the next twelve month period I will spend two months on long-term
attachment in the United States of America, at the LIGO site in
Livingston, Louisiana, and the remainder in Glasgow. My principle
goals for the following year are

\begin{itemize}
\item Complete my long-term attachment at Livingston, LA;
\item Spend a month at Georgia Institute of Technology, working on deveelopment of the Gaussian process surrogate model project;
\item Conduct investigations for handling non-stationarity in the parameter space of training data for Gaussian processes, with the aim of impoving the precision of this method for informing future sampling plans
\item Complete work on the paper describing the sampling plan method
\item Start investigations into using Gaussian processes to improve the precision of burst searches
\item Complete work on the sGRB beaming paper [carried over from year 1, with some progress]
\item Complete work on paper describing an Einstein delay-based method for detecting neutron stars
\item Complete work on a test suite for Minke
\item Implement numerical relativity BBH waveforms, and accretion disk instabilities in Minke
\end{itemize}

